Found this place off Yelp while in Williamsburg and thought to check it out. Ordered the guacamole and chips, steak burrito and grilled chicken torta. The torta because I saw an image on Yelp and wanted to try it. The waiter said it's from the brunch menu and I said never mind. But he asked the chef anyway if it was possible to make for dinner and it wasn't the problem.  The guacamole needed more salt/lime, but the salsa they gave us was delicious. The burrito was nice and fat, stuffed with meat, beans and flavor. The torta was equally delicious, a massive sandwich bursting with flavor. Finally the dessert - the chocolate brownie bomb (or something like that) was delicious but my favorite was the tres leches.  Overall, the food was great and the service was on 100. Very welcoming, polite and patient staff, the waiter obviously took the extra step to cater to my cravings which I really appreciated. The decor was nice and homely, I'm definitely coming back here!
